{
  "page": "Magnar of Thenn",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Styr_Magnar_of_Thenn_TheMico.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/56/Styr_Magnar_of_Thenn_TheMico.jpg/300px-Styr_Magnar_of_Thenn_TheMico.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"424\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/5/56/Styr_Magnar_of_Thenn_TheMico.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Styr_Magnar_of_Thenn_TheMico.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Styr\" title=\"Styr\">Styr</a>, Magnar of Thenn, by TheMico ©</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Magnar of Thenn</b> is the title held by the leader of the <a href=\"/index.php/Thenns\" title=\"Thenns\">Thenns</a>, a tribe of <a href=\"/index.php/Free_folk\" title=\"Free folk\">free folk</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Thenn_(valley)\" title=\"Thenn (valley)\">Thenn valley</a> found <a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">beyond the Wall</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Frostfangs\" title=\"Frostfangs\">Frostfangs</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Known_Magnars_of_Thenn\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known Magnars of Thenn</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Magnar_of_Thenn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><i><a href=\"/index.php/Magnar\" title=\"Magnar\">Magnar</a></i> is a word in the <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Tongue\" title=\"Old Tongue\">Old Tongue</a> translated as \"<a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lord</a>\" in the <a href=\"/index.php/Common_Tongue\" title=\"Common Tongue\">Common Tongue</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Thenns\" title=\"Thenns\">Thenns</a> appear to see <a href=\"/index.php/Styr\" title=\"Styr\">Styr</a> more as a <a href=\"/index.php/God\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"God\">god</a> than a lord.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Magnar_of_Thenn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Mance Rayder</a> had to defeat <a href=\"/index.php/Styr\" title=\"Styr\">Styr</a> three times before the Magnar agreed to support him as <a href=\"/index.php/King-beyond-the-Wall\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"King-beyond-the-Wall\">King-beyond-the-Wall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd49.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd49.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Magnar_of_Thenn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Magnar_of_Thenn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Styr\" title=\"Styr\">Styr</a>, Magnar of Thenn, resents having to share authority with <a href=\"/index.php/Jarl\" title=\"Jarl\">Jarl</a> when they are sent by <a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Mance Rayder</a> to cross the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Jarl falls to his death while attempting to climb the Wall.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Styr leads the <a href=\"/index.php/Attack_on_Castle_Black\" title=\"Attack on Castle Black\">attack on Castle Black</a> but is slain when the castle's wooden stair and several tons of ice collapse on him and his men.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Styr's son <a href=\"/index.php/Sigorn\" title=\"Sigorn\">Sigorn</a>, the new Magnar of Thenn,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> is held captive by <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> after the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_beneath_the_Wall\" title=\"Battle beneath the Wall\">battle beneath the Wall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos76.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos76.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Magnar_of_Thenn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Alys_x_sigorn_by_chillyravenart.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/34/Alys_x_sigorn_by_chillyravenart.jpg/300px-Alys_x_sigorn_by_chillyravenart.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/34/Alys_x_sigorn_by_chillyravenart.jpg/450px-Alys_x_sigorn_by_chillyravenart.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/34/Alys_x_sigorn_by_chillyravenart.jpg/600px-Alys_x_sigorn_by_chillyravenart.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Alys_x_sigorn_by_chillyravenart.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Alys_Karstark\" title=\"Alys Karstark\">Alys Karstark</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Sigorn\" title=\"Sigorn\">Sigorn</a>, by Chillyravenart ©</div></div></div>\n<p>Word spreads at Castle Black that Stannis intends to grant lands and castles to wildling leaders like <a href=\"/index.php/Rattleshirt\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Rattleshirt\">Rattleshirt</a> and the Magnar of Thenn.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd3.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> Stannis considers placing wildlings led by Sigorn as his van when he departs Castle Black, but <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Night&#39;s Watch\">Lord Commander of the Night's Watch</a>, advises him against the idea.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Emmett\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Iron Emmett\">Iron Emmett</a> recommends that Jon grant one of the ruined castles of the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a> to the Thenns.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Alys_Karstark\" title=\"Alys Karstark\">Alys Karstark</a> flees <a href=\"/index.php/Karhold\" title=\"Karhold\">Karhold</a> to avoid being forced to marry her kin <a href=\"/index.php/Cregan_Karstark\" title=\"Cregan Karstark\">Cregan</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> Lord Commander Snow arranges for her to marry Sigorn. During <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_of_Sigorn_and_Alys_Karstark\" title=\"Wedding of Sigorn and Alys Karstark\">their wedding</a>, Sigorn dons arms for the newly-created <a href=\"/index.php/House_Thenn\" title=\"House Thenn\">House Thenn</a>. Alys believes that Karhold will open its gates to her and Sigorn's two hundred Thenns.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd49.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd49.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_Magnars_of_Thenn\">Known Magnars of Thenn</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Magnar_of_Thenn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known Magnars of Thenn\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Styr\" title=\"Styr\">Styr</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Sigorn\" title=\"Sigorn\">Sigorn</a>, his son.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Magnar_of_Thenn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The Magnar claimed to be the last of the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a>, and ruled with an iron hand. His little land of <a href=\"/index.php/Thenn_(valley)\" title=\"Thenn (valley)\">Thenn</a> was a high mountain valley hidden amongst the northernmost peaks of the <a href=\"/index.php/Frostfangs\" title=\"Frostfangs\">Frostfangs</a>, surrounded by <a href=\"/index.php/Cave_dwellers\" title=\"Cave dwellers\">cave dwellers</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hornfoot\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hornfoot\">Hornfoot</a> men, <a href=\"/index.php/Giants\" title=\"Giants\">giants</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Ice-river_clans\" title=\"Ice-river clans\">cannibal clans of the ice rivers</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Ygritte\" title=\"Ygritte\">Ygritte</a> said the <a href=\"/index.php/Thenns\" title=\"Thenns\">Thenns</a> were savage fighters, and that their Magnar was a <a href=\"/index.php/God\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"God\">god</a> to them. Jon could believe that. Unlike <a href=\"/index.php/Jarl\" title=\"Jarl\">Jarl</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Harma\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Harma\">Harma</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Rattleshirt\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Rattleshirt\">Rattleshirt</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Styr\" title=\"Styr\">Styr</a> commanded absolute obedience from his men, and that discipline was no doubt part of why <a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Mance</a> had chosen him to go over the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Styr\" title=\"Styr\">The Magnar</a> is a ruler, not a raider.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Emmett</b>: You might do well to bestow a castle on the Magnar.<br />\n</p><p><b>Jon</b>: I might if I could trust him. <a href=\"/index.php/Sigorn\" title=\"Sigorn\">Sigorn</a> blames me for his father's death, I fear. Worse, he was bred and trained to give orders, not to take them. Do not confuse the <a href=\"/index.php/Thenns\" title=\"Thenns\">Thenns</a> with <a href=\"/index.php/Free_folk\" title=\"Free folk\">free folk</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Magnar\" title=\"Magnar\">Magnar</a> means <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lord</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Tongue\" title=\"Old Tongue\">Old Tongue</a>, I am told, but <a href=\"/index.php/Styr\" title=\"Styr\">Styr</a> was closer to a god to his people, and his son is cut from the same skin. I do not require men to kneel, but they do need to obey.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Emmett</b>: Aye, m'lord, but you had best do something with the Magnar. You'll have trouble with the Thenns if you ignore them.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Emmett\" title=\"Emmett\">Emmett</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">Jon Snow</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Magnar_of_Thenn&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:2; -moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n